y, those at the very apex influencing the spirits that govern the ebbs and tides of the city's corporate systems. Perhaps more alluring to some members that climb beyond the first rungs of the ladder is the knowledge and wisdom the spirits of Miami has to offer, shared only to those that are capable of coaxing it from them.%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c !!! %25vampire%25 '''Temple:'''%0a%3c None yet.%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c !!! %25vampire%25 '''Methods:'''%0a%3c Everything the Invisible Hand does, it does to further its own agenda, broadening its influence over the spirit realm and the physical realm of Miami. Members are expected to be discrete as to not draw the attention of their competitors or spark rivalries with other factions that delve the Shadow. The lower ranked members are guided on a path of discovery of the ephemeral, but are also expected to contribute on their own part to the cult. Indeed, many Investors are simply that: investors. They provide much needed funds, gaining only tidbits of preternatural insights in return. Yet those that truly aspire, those who seek to understand and manipulate the realm beyond ours, they will truly find bountiful rewards.%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c !!! %25vampire%25'''Cult Members'''%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c ||! Image ||! Name ||! Rank ||! Venue ||%0a%3c || https://i.imgur.com/4g2CBsH.jpg || %25newwin%25 '''[[https://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/Players/VictoriaMessini|Victoria]]''' || '''Ascended (•••••)''' || %25vampire%25 '''Vampire''' ||%0a%3c || https://i.imgur.com/kxcJmcp.jpg || %25newwin%25 '''[[https://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/Players/LoreleiMcCowan|Lorelei]]''' || '''Ascended (•••••)''' || %25vampire%25 '''Vampire''' ||%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c !!! %25vampire%25'''Ranks'''%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Investor (•):''' The first thing the Invisible Hand does is ensure that the spirits they’ve allied with work to cover the tracks of any of their maneuvering in the city. Every Investor is hard to track down as a result and gain the Untouchable (•) merit. \\%0a%3c '''Investor (••):''' Investors expect a certain amount of return for their labors in the Organization. The first signs of their reward are the loyal staff that they accrue to assist them. Of course, the Kindred often see these individuals as a better source of food than labor. Gain a dot of the Staff (•) or Herd (•) merit.  \\%0a%3c '''Priest (•••):''' At this level the hints of supernatural power that were introduced before become clear. The priests and priestesses of the City Father are taught to recognize his messages and guide the cult's actions, gaining the Communion (••) merit. \\%0a%3c '''Archpriest (••••):''' Spirits are not the only beings that guide the living, the voices of the dead also carrying their wisdom. As priests rise towards the top of the Invisible hand, some familiarize themselves with the nature of ghosts, while other continues to hone their understanding of spirits. They gain either the Medium (•••) merit OR Spirit Speech (••) and Area of Expertise (Occult: Spirits).  \\%0a%3c '''Ascended (•••••):''' The Ascended of the Invisible Hand know and see the truth, the cult existing as much as an extension of the City Father’s will as it does in an effort to extend influence over Him in order to further their own goals and machinations. Ascended Kindred or ghouls gain a dot of Blood Tenebrous. Others at this rank simply benefit from increased influence and connections in the City’s spiritual realms, gaining Allies: Spirits (•••).%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Suggested promotion justifications:''' Go on a sojourn into the Shadow, partake in rituals devoted to spirits, discern the intents of Father City and further its goals, discover a previously unknown Loci, obtain occult knowledge about spirits or ghosts.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:include GameRef.Directorycity:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
